synchronized. Inside such clusters, the simulated {\{}BOLD{\}} signal between nodes is found to be correlated, instantiating the empirically observed {\{}RSNs{\}}. Between clusters, patterns of positive and negative correlations are observed, as described in experimental studies. These results are found to be robust with respect to a biologically plausible range of model parameters. In conclusion, our model suggests how resting-state neural activity can originate from the interplay between the local neural dynamics and the large-scale structure of the brain. Copyright $\backslash$copyright 2011 Elsevier Inc. All rights reserved.},
